== 2. Bg2 ==
{{Chess Opening Theory/Position|=
|Grob's Gambit|
}}
White fianchettos the bishop, gambiting the pawn on g4 as there's no actual way to defend it. In exchange they have a few tricks up their sleeve. Black usually accepts the gambit by taking the free pawn with [[/2...Bxg4/]].

